args: After Yukimura learned of Jinpachi's strengths\nand weaknesses, a bond of trust was forged\nbetween the pair.
Yukimura continued to connect with her vassals,\nand before she knew it, people from all walks of\nlife gathered to honor her.
But one day, one of her trusted vassals—a ninja\nnamed Sasuke—arrived with troubling news.
Indeed. And based on their current actions,\nit's likely they plan to launch an invasion\non this very castle!
The Mukuroshu are the dogs that revived\nTsukuyomi and attempted to overthrow\nthe shogunate.

The fact they're planning to invade a
Wyrmclan leader's castle tells us they
haven't given up on the second part of
that particular plan.
You and Jinpachi were attacked recently.\nright? Those assassins may also have\nbeen remnants of the Mukuroshu.
Thaaaaaat's it! Time to get out there and\nshow those creepos who's boss!
Pray allow me to concoct the plan of\nattack, milady, for I already have a fine\nidea ready to be put in motion.
With our combined powers,\nthis castle will NEVER fall!
According to our prior reconnaissance,\nYukimura's castle has weak defenses in\nthe back. If we attack there, we...
Huh? Wait, hang on. There's something\ndifferent about the castle now...
What the hell?! There's a smaller castle\nin front of the real one!
So they WERE planning on attacking our\nweak point. Good that we devised that\ncountermeasure.
But having us create a new castle in less\nthan ten days was asking the impossible.
And yet you did it, because every last one\nof you is FREAKIN' AMAZING!
For you, Lady Yukimura, we would put\nour all into whatever must be done.
But now is when the real plan begins:\nWe hold the castle while picking off\ntheir forces one by one.
Ha ha ha! Look at 'em run!
WE DID IT! We protected the castle\nand totally kicked their dumb butts!
(Our enemy retreated the moment they\nsaw they were at a disadvantage. It seems\nthey're more clever than I first thought.)
(This may not be our last battle...)
So now what? Without that weak point,\nthere's no way for us to take the castle!
We merely need to fight their tactics\nwith some of our own.
Ready the catapults! We'll hit them\njust as we did before.
But there aren't any catapults in the\narea they're targeting!
Blast. The branch castle was built so\nhastily, we didn't have time to put\ncatapults in every location.
But how did they know exactly where to\nattack? How did they find our weakness?
No one outside this castle would know\nwhich areas lacked catapults.
(Oh dear. We cannot afford to let morale\nfall now...but what to do about it?!)
I KNOW there's no traitor among us,\nbecause you're all comrades I trust!
Then how did they know our weak point?
Gya! That bird vanished! What in the world\nis happening here, milady?!
That bird was a shikigami controlled\nby an onmyoji.
Seimei told me about those folks.\nHe said they use shikigami for\nreconnaissance.
So THAT'S how they managed to get\ninformation on our weakness!
See? I told you there was no traitor!\nNow get those spirits up so we can\ntake these chumps DOOOOOWN!
I believe in all of you, which means\nthere's no WAY you can lose!
(Lady Yukimura's unwavering sentiments\nhave saved us once again.)
(Her feelings have reached the soldiers\nand bolstered morale. Now's our chance!)
Lady Yukimura, how does this plan sound\nto drive the enemy away?
We're gonna take these guys out once\nand for all, so I need ALL of you to lend\nme your strength!
Hmm... My shikigami has gone silent.\nIt can't have been discovered, can it?
No matter—we have the information we\nneed. If we keep focusing on that weak\npoint, we can finally seize the castle!
The enemy has swarmed our weak point,\nwhich means we can easily surround them!
Impossible! They stopped holding the\ncastle and charged our position instead?!
Never mind! Don't falter! Fight back!
You don't stand a chance now that we've\nbeen bolstered by Lady Yukimura!
We defeated the enemy without a single\ncasualty. It is a flawless victory.
And it's all thanks to all of you!\nHip hip, YOU GUYS!
C'mon, now! Join in! Hip hip...
